@djangocre

Exactly. The reputational damage for them would be so massive that, instead of taking that hit, they’ll have to make the right decision and turn it in their favor. If they let a person who bought $40,000 worth of shares win $20 million, it will be all over the global news. If they decide to “screw him over,” that will also be all over the global news - but with a very different angle.

We’re only just getting started; we still have three days ahead of us. For the skeptics: Polymarket can override UMA’s decision, and it has done so in the past.
